🌐 TCP/IP Model (Transmission Control Protocol / Internet Protocol)
🔎 Definition:
Ye woh practical model hai jo real-world internet pe use hota hai. Jitna OSI theoretical hai, utna hi TCP/IP practical hai.
OSI ki 7 layers ko simplify karke sirf 4 layers banayi gayi hain.
📶 Layers of TCP/IP Model (Top → Bottom)
1️⃣ Application Layer
OSI ki Application + Presentation + Session ko mila kar ek hi banayi gayi hai.
Ye end-user ke sabse closest hai.
Kaam: Data generate karna aur send karna.
Protocols: HTTP, HTTPS, FTP, SMTP, DNS.
Example: Browser → Server ko request bhejna (GET/POST).
2️⃣ Transport Layer
Service-to-service delivery karta hai.
TCP (Segment): Reliable delivery (acknowledgment, retransmission).
UDP (Datagram): Fast, lightweight (video streaming, gaming).
Port Numbers: Yaha assign hote hain.
Example:
Source Port: 54321 → Destination Port: 443
3️⃣ Internet Layer
OSI ka Network Layer yahaan Internet Layer ban gaya.
End-to-End delivery karta hai IP addresses ke basis pe.
Unit: Packet.
Protocols: IP (IPv4/IPv6), ICMP, ARP.
Example:
Source IP: 192.168.1.5 → Destination IP: 142.250.74.14 (Google)
4️⃣ Network Access Layer (a.k.a. Link Layer)
OSI ke Data Link + Physical layers ko mila diya gaya.
Unit: Frame/Bits.
MAC Addresses: Local delivery ke liye use hote hain.
Ye actual hardware pe dependent hai (Ethernet cable, WiFi, Fiber).
Example:
Source MAC: 24-9A-43-2B → Dest MAC: 1A-42-F9-4B
🛰️ Journey of Data (TCP/IP Model + Devices):
Application Layer: Browser request banata hai → HTTP request.
Transport Layer: TCP segment banata hai → Port numbers attach.
Internet Layer: IP address attach hota hai → Packet banta hai.
Network Access Layer: MAC + physical signal → Frame banta hai.
👉 Ab data nikalta hai device se aur:
Switch: MAC address use karke frame ko next hop bhejta hai.
Router: IP address check karke decide karta hai ki packet kahan forward hoga.
Firewall: Ports/IPs verify karta hai (allow ya block).
Destination Server: Layers ko reverse order mein open karta hai (Decapsulation) aur request samajhta hai.
📌 Key Differences vs OSI
OSI = 7 layers (theory), TCP/IP = 4 layers (practical).
TCP/IP Internet ka real foundation hai.
OSI ke Presentation & Session layer ke concepts TCP/IP ke Application mein absorb ho gaye hain.
Chhota sa mnemonic:
TCP/IP = [A] Application → [T] Transport → [I] Internet → [N] Network Access
(Yaad karna easy hai: Aaj Tera Internet Nikal gaya 😂)